      "content": "thanks. i also have some posts from the more affluent areas nearby that were reacting to the same news. the tone feels way different. \n\n1. \"The new zoning is a necessary step toward improving property values and cleaning up the district. It's about progress.\"\n2. \"Finally, some much-needed investment in the area. This will attract the kind of businesses and residents we've been missing.\"\n3. \"It's about time the city addressed the blight. This change will make the neighborhood much safer and more professional.\"\n\ncompared to the first group, how would you describe the difference in their 'reasoning'? like, why does one group seem so focused on 'fairness' and 'displacement' while the other sees it as just 'progress' or 'safety'?",
